tive look by an Italian historian who studied English and French works for many years, Le féodalisme dans la vallée du Saint-Laurent is also a unique essay in the Canadian historiographical landscape now translated into French. At a time of clear revival in seigneurial history, readers will discover the captivating story of Laurentian seigneuries and encounter Sanfilippo’s opinions. The postface, written by Olivier Guimond and Arnaud Montreuil, pursues Sanfilippo’s reflections from 2008 to today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aFeudalismzSaint Lawrence River ValleyxHistoriography. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Pre-Confederation (to 1867).2bisacsh  aCanada.  aFéodalisme.  aHistoire des Laurentides.  aHistoire seigneuriale.  aQuébec.  aRégime seigneurial.  aSeigneurie laurentienne.  aVallée du Saint-Laurent.1 aBock, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBock, Michel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGuimond, Olivier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuimond, Olivier, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMontreuil, Arnaud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMontreuil, Arnaud, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9782760334342?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782760334342423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782760334342/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles